\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs16\b\insrsid2427393 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 User Interface (Tkinter-based):
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2427393 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Responsible for creating the graphical user interface (GUI).\line Built using Tkinter, a Python library for creating GUI applications.\line 
Allows users to interact with the system, including video upload and system controls.\line Authentication Module (TKinter):
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Manages user authentication and access control.\line Implemented using Flask for back-end functionality.\line Tkinter is used for rendering the login page dynamically and handling user interactions.\line 
Video Upload & Preprocessing (}{\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2427393 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  HYPERLINK "https://www.pythonprojectz.com/opencv-projects/" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4852467 
{\*\datafield 
00d0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b0200000003000000e0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b78000000680074007400700073003a002f002f007700770077002e0070007900740068006f006e00700072006f006a006500630074007a002e0063006f006d002f006f00700065006e00630076002d00700072006f00
6a0065006300740073002f000000795881f43b1d7f48af2c825dc485276300000000a5ab00030073}}}{\fldrslt {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\ul\cf2\insrsid2427393 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 OpenCV}}}\sectd \ltrsect\linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2427393 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 ):
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Handles the uploading of video files by authenticated users.\line Uses OpenCV, a computer vision library, for video processing.\line 
Extracts individual frames from the uploaded video at 30 FPS, which serves as input for subsequent processing modules.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs16\b\insrsid2427393 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Lane Detection Module (OpenCV):
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2427393 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Identifies and tracks road lane markings within the video frames.\line Utilizes OpenCV's image processing and contour analysis capabilities.\line 
Applies Gaussian blur, Canny edge detection, and contour analysis for accurate lane tracking.\line Veh\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 icle Detection Module (YOLOv8 + TensorFlow):
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Detects and tracks surrounding vehicles in real-time.\line Uses YOLOv8 (You Only Look Once) deep learning model for object detection.\line 
TensorFlow is employed for executing the YOLOv8 model and processing the results.\line Distance Estimation Module (NumPy):
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Estimates the distance to the preceding vehicle for collision avoidance.\line Combines the size of detected vehicles in pixels with camera calibration parameters using NumPy.\line 
Geometric calculations are performed to determine \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 real-world distance.\line Alert System (Pygame, PyAudio):
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Activates visual and audio alerts when the estimated distance to the preceding vehicle is below a safety threshold.\line Pygame is used for rendering visual alerts, such as warning icons.\line 
PyAudio plays collision alarm MP3 sounds for audio alerts.\line Steering Whee\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 l Simulation (PyGame):
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2427393 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid2427393\charrsid2427393 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
Simulates the movement of the steering wheel based on lane positions detected by the Lane Detection module. Pygame renders the steering wheel sprite using OpenGL transformations.\line E\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
nhances user engagement and provides a realistic representation of steering angles induced by lane curvature changes.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Integration & User Interaction (Multiprocessing):
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Ensures the concurrent execution of all modules for a responsive real-time simulation.\line Multiprocessing is used to manage parallel processing, allowing modules to run concurrently.\line 
Users can interact with the simulation through the Tkinter interface.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Stearing WHeel CNN algorithm Matrics
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 284/284 [==============================] - 1s 3ms/step\line Pr\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ecision: 0.763170188220263\line Recall: 0.8735961242017177\line F1 Score: 0.8146581628369097\line Accuracy: 0.8735961242017177

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Yolo Matrics\line Precision: 0.57\line \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Accuracy: 63\line F1 Score: 0.59\line Recall: 0.53
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Yolo Paper: https://www.cv-foundation.org/openaccess/content_cvpr_2016/papers/Redmon_You_Only_Look_CVPR_2016_paper.pdf
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Dataset: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1zm7VSRCsYHmKqEpZHe-TDNogYEf_pfTp?usp=sharing
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\fs24\insrsid2427393\charrsid2427393 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Doubts Related to Autonomous Car Driving and Driver Drowsiness and Alert System:-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid2427393\charrsid2427393 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Question 1: How did you validate the results?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Answer: To validate the results and assess accuracy, we employed a standard practice of splitting the dataset into training and te\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
sting sets. The model was trained on the training set, and subsequently, the testing data was utilized to evaluate and validate the accuracy of the model.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Dataset Link: https://github.com/SullyChen/driving-datasets
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Question 2: What is your motivation to use this dataset?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
Answer: My motivation to use this dataset stems from completing the Self-Driving Car Engineer Nanodegree. Through this course, I gained insights and exposure that motivated me to implement a system using the provided dataset.\line https://www.ud
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 acity.com/course/self-driving-car-engineer-nanodegree--nd0013
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Question 3: How do you ensure the model is not overfitted?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid4852467 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid2427393\charrsid2427393 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
Answer: To prevent overfitting, we implemented several strategies. Firstly, we carefully curated and verified the dataset, eliminating noisy data. Additionally, we utilized a reduced number of epochs during training and employed proper loss computation te
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 chniques. Data augmentation was applied to enhance the model's ability to handle diverse scenarios. Furthermore, the incorporation of a \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
dropout layer played a crucial role in mitigating the risk of overfitting during the training process}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid2427393\charrsid4852467 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13260272 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid13260272 
